Reasoning: 
1. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper focuses on social media inference and learning representations of individuals from social network data. 
2. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - The paper uses natural language processing techniques to extract textual information about individuals. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper proposes a neural network-based approach for learning representations of individuals. 
4. cs.SD (Software Engineering) - The paper discusses the scalability of the proposed approach to large datasets. 
5. cs.CY (Computers and Society) - The paper addresses the social computing task of inferring latent attributes of people online.
